00074 const char* regressionTest(const BinaryDataEncoder::Config& config)
00075 {
00076     if (config.precision == BinaryDataEncoder::Precision_32 &&
00077         config.byteOrder == BinaryDataEncoder::ByteOrder_LittleEndian)
00078         return sampleEncoded32Little_;
00079 
00080     if (config.precision == BinaryDataEncoder::Precision_32 &&
00081         config.byteOrder == BinaryDataEncoder::ByteOrder_BigEndian)
00082         return sampleEncoded32Big_;
00083 
00084     if (config.precision == BinaryDataEncoder::Precision_64 &&
00085         config.byteOrder == BinaryDataEncoder::ByteOrder_LittleEndian)
00086         return sampleEncoded64Little_;
00087 
00088     if (config.precision == BinaryDataEncoder::Precision_64 &&
00089         config.byteOrder == BinaryDataEncoder::ByteOrder_BigEndian)
00090         return sampleEncoded64Big_;
00091      
00092     throw runtime_error("[BinaryDataEncoderTest::regressionTest()] Untested configuration.");
00093 }

00096 void testConfiguration(const BinaryDataEncoder::Config& config)
00097 {
00098     if (os_)
00099         *os_ << "testConfiguration: " << config << endl;
00100 
00101     // initialize scan data
00102 
00103     vector<double> binary(sampleDataSize_);
00104     copy(sampleData_, sampleData_+sampleDataSize_, binary.begin());
00105 
00106     if (os_)
00107     {
00108         *os_ << "original: " << binary.size() << endl;
00109         *os_ << setprecision(20) << fixed;
00110         copy(binary.begin(), binary.end(), ostream_iterator<double>(*os_, "\n")); 
00111     }
00112 
00113     // instantiate encoder
00114 
00115     BinaryDataEncoder encoder(config);
00116 
00117     // encode
00118 
00119     string encoded;
00120     encoder.encode(binary, encoded);
00121 
00122     if (os_)
00123         *os_ << "encoded: " << encoded.size() << endl << encoded << endl;
00124 
00125     // regression testing for encoding
00126 
00127     unit_assert(encoded == regressionTest(config));
00128 
00129     // decode
00130 
00131     vector<double> decoded;
00132     encoder.decode(encoded, decoded);
00133 
00134     if (os_)
00135     {
00136         *os_ << "decoded: " << decoded.size() << endl;
00137         copy(decoded.begin(), decoded.end(), ostream_iterator<double>(*os_, "\n")); 
00138     }
00139 
00140     // validate by comparing scan data before/after encode/decode
00141 
00142     unit_assert(binary.size() == decoded.size());
00143     const double epsilon = 1e-5; 
00144     for (vector<double>::const_iterator it=binary.begin(), jt=decoded.begin();  
00145          it!=binary.end(); ++it, ++jt)
00146     {
00147         unit_assert_equal(*it, *jt, epsilon);
00148     }
00149 
00150     if (os_) *os_ << "validated with epsilon: " << epsilon << "\n\n";
00151 }
